From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 21:04:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Refactor site content to match real Skandha Constructions
 company profile

- Remove machinery-leasing/equipment-fleet business entirely: delete
  Equipment.tsx, its nav link, EQUIPMENT/SERVICES dead data, and every
  "180+ Machine Fleet / Browse Equipment Fleet / Fleet ready for lease"
  reference across Hero, About, Contact and the chatbot.
- Update company stats: 420+ -> 160+ projects, 4 -> 12 engineers,
  40+ -> 80+ labourers; rebalanced the Stats grid for 5 cards.
- Replace the trusted-clients marquee with the real project list
  (Minnal M Mahal, Thangasaras Kalyana Mandapam, Valliyammal Mahal,
  PWD, Funmall, ITC WelcomHotel) and rewrote the 6 project case
  studies around these real names instead of fictional clients.
- Remove all ISO/HSE/LEED certification content, keeping only the
  standalone "Government Class-A" claim.
- Rewrote testimonials to drop fake names/titles/ratings, attributing
  each quote to its project instead.
- Enlarged the navbar logo ~34% without shifting nav links or buttons.
- Removed the Hero's JCB background photo, keeping the gradient,
  particles and floating cards.
- Swapped in construction-in-progress imagery for the "Ongoing"
  portfolio cards only; completed cards untouched.
- Rebuilt the chatbot's knowledge base/intents around the real
  company facts and removed all fleet/ISO/fake-company answers.
- Cleaned up unused imports and non-optimized <img> usage in the
  unrelated /feed demo module, and removed now-orphaned image assets.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
